# CODEOWNERS — review ownership for MedScale.
#
# Solo-maintained today. The path rules below are intentional, not decorative: they
# encode which areas demand extra scrutiny (governance, decisions, scientific policy,
# data licensing) and pre-wire GitHub review routing for when the project opens to
# outside contributors — so review discipline is enforced from the first external PR,
# not retrofitted later.

# Default owner for everything.
*                       @IamShehri

# Governance, architecture decisions, and scientific policy.
# Changes here alter how MedScale is run or what it claims — maintainer review always.
/docs/governance/       @IamShehri
/docs/adr/              @IamShehri
/docs/research/         @IamShehri
/docs/vision/           @IamShehri

# Data provenance and licensing (Rule R3). Licence-sensitive; never rubber-stamped.
/data/                  @IamShehri

# Public API surface and reproducibility spine — stability-critical.
/src/medscale/          @IamShehri

# Packaging, release, and CI/CD surface.
/pyproject.toml         @IamShehri
/.github/               @IamShehri
